        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         A necro trying to duel a level 60 well equipped melee is going to die.</P><P>A spectre pet trying to hit a level 60 monk will hit for around 7dmg when it does connect.  Lifetaps and dots do 2/3rds of what they are supposed to.  Fear/root/snare will never land.  Screaming terror does land on people with crap resists.  Staff of the silent star only procs for 2/3rds damage also so trying to melee your way out isn't going to do it either.</P><P>Hardest class to beat is now a ranger on a horse.  They'll tear you to shreads with a bow out of range of your spells.  Spectre pet is such a gimp that I'd not waste the mana when gate takes a lot less to cast.  A bard will still kill most classes in a duel but a ranger hits for around 230 with a bow.</P><P>It used to be that in duels wizards kicked the junk out of most classes.  They need to re-evaluate the old rules for PvP so it comes into line again.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

