        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Drainer, if a necro loses to to warrior they have some problems. Say you have a lvl 60 warrior duel a lvl 60 necro, the necro should win hands down. The only way a necro would lose is if they were to try and tank the warrior. jboots, dot warrior, let pet attack him and run around. The biggest mistakes warriors make when dueling is they will turn around and attack your pet, baaaaad idea. </P><P>When they do turn round and turn their attention to your pet, then you just sit there and dot the hell out of em. Warriors are the easiet class to duel by far. Rogues can also be very easy because all they can do is tank, and even then they do not have the hp and ac to where they can tank up front for very long. With a rogue you do the exact same thing as you do with a warrior. Remember, warriors and rogues have to get up close to you to do any real damage, just keep your distance (gate, shadow step, levant) and you will end the fight with full hp.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
