        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="30865"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;05/22/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 03:05:08</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=1409"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1409')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=30865&amp;TOPIC_ID=3940&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Duels&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I get a kick out of dueling too, but only on my safe and secure bluebie server.  The zeks scare me.</P><P>The only classes that give me trouble in duels these days are extremely well geared Paladins and Monks.  This is assuming the duel is "fair" and melee can't use golem wands, pumice, etc. and wizards/necros aren't using Manaburn and Lifeburn.</P><P>Paladins are difficult for two main reasons.  1) You have to kill them 2-3 times over and 2) Two-handed bash is a freaking nightmare of interrupts.  You HAVE to spend alot of time annuling them to kill their sickly efficient DOT heals.  I often use a trick where i cast a super cheap low level fire DOT and see if they dispell it - can somtimes lead to you winning the mana game and getting the kill when they go OOM.  Pyre is also nice as it does damage so fast you can get some good punch relatively fast.  A good tactic is to mix it up...sometimes use the cheap one, sometimes the nasty.</P><P>Monks are really only difficult if they've aquired an Abashi Stick from Vulak, which makes them virtually impossible.  With it they can pretty much negate anything you do to them and can cause all sorts of problems pillaging you over and over again (killing vexing for example).  You need 3 instants up constantly to simply keep it away from anything you want.  The major problem with monks is they generate tons of interrupts from character movement.  Monks move you far more than any other class in my experience, which leads to much higher interrupt rates.  I can nearly defeat Rogues and Rangers standing toe-to-toe chain casting Deflux, but not the case with monks - I have to run constantly.</P><P>Mage pets are tough, but totally workable.  Once their pet is controlled you win.</P><P>Rogue backstab can be rough at the wrong time.  Beyond that it's pretty hard to lose to a rogue.</P><P>Rangers.  Arrows hurt and they can outrange you, but after a few shadowsteps you'll find them and burn them down.  And, frankly, if a ranger fights you like this...it's a bit unfair anyway (there's no 2/3 penalty, it has ridiculous range and does spell-equivalent damage).</P><P>Shadowknights are super dangerous because they have many of the same abilities we have (namely lifetaps), plus eating a game ending HT when low on hp and you're cooked.  I'd rank them the third toughest for a Necro.</P><P>Warriors.  Tough all around.  I rarely lose, but I'm almost always low on mana and health afterwards.  DOT and run.</P><P>Bards can be tough but in my experience they simply can't deal enough melee damage to be a serious threat up close and they will die quickly to lifetaps if they try to kite you.</P><P>Wizards just can't kill you fast enough unless they get a break with a lure critical.  Likewise, if you crit a ToN they are toast.  A pet just makes it harder for them.</P><P>Shaman and Druids can be tough with the healing, but you will win the mana game 9 times out of 10.</P><P>I've never "dueled" a cleric or beastlord and have only poked at a few enchanters.</P><P>Savan<BR>Afterlife</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

