        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BR>Maybe I've just fought good melees.</P><P>They don't touch the pet, ever. They run after me, while pet trails behind like a gimp. If they're smart, they have shit buffs like grim aura and see invis bracer behind a Sow potion, and spam the pre-nerf pumices and the golem wands. Once you stop to cast, they hit you hard, kick to stun, and make you pay for that gimpy dot you land on them.</P><P>They outlive the dot(easily), and keep on hitting you with arrows while you try to SS and run around hills trees to get spells off.</P><P>Lifetaps land 2/3.</P><P>BTW, you stop to cast once against a rogue and you die. They just /discipline and 2x backstab you and loot.</P><P>Necros 1-50 are pk machines, its not even a contest, we destroy everyone. 51-60 Necros are a joke in pvp.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
